title: London tube breaks into rousing rendition of 'Lean on Me'
text:
London tube breaks into rousing rendition of 'Lean on Me' Last updated 10:33, October 9 2015 Scott Ross/YouTube 
Lean on me performed on the London Underground 
Don't make eye contact - it's an unwritten rule when travelling on the London Underground, but passengers on the Northern Line turned this commute into one to remember. 
Breaking out into a mass singalong of Bill Withers' 1972 hit Lean On Me , song, the commuters sang and danced in the carriage. Two travellers even played the guitar and the violin. 
Maybe the tube ain't so bad. YOUTUBE/SCREENGRAB
